{"data":{"markdownRemark":null,"npmPackage":{"name":"gatsby-source-twitter","description":"Fetch data from Twitter API","keywords":["gatsby","gatsbyjs","gatsby-plugin","twitter"],"lastPublisher":{"name":"g100g","avatar":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/39b2c9f6b46612250740f44109a39a45"},"repository":{"url":"https://github.com/G100g/gatsby-source-twitter"},"readme":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-source-twitter\"><a href=\"#gatsby-source-twitter\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-source-twitter</h1>\n<p>Source plugin for pulling data into Gatsby from Twitter Search API.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// In your gatsby-config.js</span>\nmodule<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-source-twitter`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>           \n            q<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`@wesbos`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>    \n            credentials<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                consumer_key<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"INSERT_HERE_YOUR_CONSUMER_KEY\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                consumer_secret<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"INSERT_HERE_YOUR_CONSUMER_SECRETE\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                bearer_token<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"INSERT_HERE_YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN\"</span>\n            <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n            tweet_mode<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'extended'</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h2 id=\"plugin-options\"><a href=\"#plugin-options\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Plugin options</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>q</strong>: A search query. Reference to <a href=\"https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/tweets/search/api-reference/get-search-tweets\">Twitter Search Tweets API</a></li>\n<li><strong>count</strong>: Number of tweet <em>(default 100)</em></li>\n<li><strong>credential</strong>: You have to create an <a href=\"https://apps.twitter.com/\">App on Twitter</a> and creating a bearer token following this <a href=\"https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/basics/authentication/api-reference/token\">instructions</a> using your consumer key and consumer secret</li>\n<li><strong>tweet_mode</strong>: Define how tweets are rendered. Possible values <code class=\"language-text\">compat</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">extended</code> (default: <code class=\"language-text\">compat</code>) <a href=\"https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/tweets/tweet-updates#consumption\">More Details</a></li>\n<li><strong>result_type</strong>: Default <code class=\"language-text\">mixed</code>, could be <code class=\"language-text\">mixed</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">recent</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">popular</code></li>\n<li><strong>fetchAllResults</strong>: Fetch all pages result</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-query-your-tweets-data-using-graphql\"><a href=\"#how-to-query-your-tweets-data-using-graphql\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to query your Tweets data using GraphQL</h2>\n<p>Below is a sample query for fetching all Tweets nodes. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"graphql\">\n      <pre class=\"language-graphql\"><code class=\"language-graphql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">query</span> PageQuery <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    allTweet <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        edges <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            node <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                created_at\n                text\n                user <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                    name\n                <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Warning</strong>: <code class=\"language-text\">id</code> field is not the tweet id, but Gatbsy internal node id. Use <code class=\"language-text\">id_str</code> if you need to use the tweet id</p>\n</blockquote>","timeToRead":1}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/packages/gatsby-source-twitter/","id":"f1a9d996-17b7-50be-9de4-a06d3745eb92"}}